Ventral side of body (
Fig. 62
) overall densely and moderately coarsely punctate only central part sparsely punctate with large shiny impunctate areas. Lateral sides of abdominal ventrite I very densely punctate with small punctures; remaining ones densely punctate with small punctures in anterolateral corners and then gradually sparser punctate inwards and apically, but with larger punctures (
